                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d253">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00 Congress, Communist International, VII/54:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BWC1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-19T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 19, 1935—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>189. Your 357, August 18, 3 p.m.<note n="57" xml:id="d253fn57">Not
                        printed.</note> In view of departure of the President shortly from
                    Washington, perhaps at end of present week <pb facs="0349" n="243"
                        xml:id="pg_243"/> Department would like to have your recommendations and
                    suggestions immediately upon close of Congress, by Wednesday the 21st if
                    possible. In view of information which you have already forwarded, Department
                    doubts that speeches and resolutions of concluding sessions of the Congress will
                    be of material importance in connection with your consideration of the
                    matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
